The paper discusses the use of reinforcement learning for robotic tasks, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also introduces a novel approach for action selection, which involves machine learning techniques such as value iteration and softmax regression, indicating a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of simulations and physical robots, suggesting a focus on systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the use of physical variables such as robot pose and distances to obstacles, indicating a potential focus on computer vision (cs.CV).
